11 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 62 O.S. 2021, Section 2401, as
12 amended by Section 2, Chapter 375, O.S.L. 2024 (62 O.S. Supp. 2024,
13 Section 2401), is amended to read as follows:
14 Section 2401. A. The Oklahoma Center for the Advancement of
15 Science and Technology (OCAST) State Treasurer shall create an
16 “Invest In Oklahoma” program to provide entities in this state with
17 funds for opportunities to invest in Oklahoma-based private equity
18 funds, venture capital funds and growth funds, and direct
19 investments in Oklahoma companies. Opportunities for investment
20 shall also include private equity funds, venture capital funds and
21 growth funds that make substantial investments in this state.
